               <msContents>
                  <summary>Missal. F<locus target="#2r">fols. 2r, </locus>-19r: Office Prayers. F<locus target="#19r">19r, </locus>-52v: Ordinary of the Mass. F<locus target="#53r">53r, </locus>-68r: Anaphora of the Apostles. F<locus target="#68r">68r, </locus>-73v: Anaphora of our Lord Jesus Christ. F<locus target="#73v">73v, </locus>-77v: Anaphora of Dioscorus. F<locus target="#77v">77v, </locus>-85v: Anaphora of John Chrysostom. F<locus target="#85v">85v, </locus>-101r: Anaphora of Our Lady Mary, attributed to Cyriacus of Behensa. F<locus target="#101r">101r</locus>-110v: Anaphora of James of Sarug, incomplete at the end.  With musical notation. (with information from Macomber catalogue)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="2r" to="110v" facs="001">Fols 2r–110v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1960Mashaf">Maṣḥafa
                                                  qǝddāse</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <notatedMusic><desc>with musical notation</desc></notatedMusic>
                </msItem>
